message.content:
One of the most significant events that happened in Lithuania in the past 5 years is the election of Gitanas Nausėda as the President of Lithuania in May 2019. Nausėda, an economist, became the country's fifth president and succeeded Dalia Grybauskaitė.

During his presidency, Nausėda has been involved in various important developments, such as responding to the COVID-19 pandemic, supporting economic growth, advancing bilateral relations with neighboring countries, and promoting Lithuania's interests within the European Union. Additionally, his presidency has witnessed significant political changes, including shifts in the representation of the ruling party and its policies.

The election of Gitanas Nausėda as President and the subsequent changes in the political landscape have had a lasting impact on Lithuania and continue to shape the country's direction and policies in various domains.
